+## Completed-task archival policy
+
+Normal completed real work should be archived, not deleted, after the retention window so
+ordinary board views stay focused while `kanban_show` and explicit archived lists continue to
+work. The operator archival command is dry-run by default and only targets request-indexed
+Kanban tasks whose status is `done` and whose `completed_at` (falling back to `created_at`) is
+older than the retention window. The default retention is 14 days.
+
+```sh
+agent-request-archive-completed --board agent-requests --retention-days 14
+agent-request-archive-completed --board agent-requests --retention-days 14 --apply
+```
+
+Deletion remains a separate incident-cleanup path for obvious smoke/test artifacts or
+sensitive accidents and should use a DB backup plus integrity checks before reporting success.
+
 ## Backup and board state
 
 Nest's full Hermes backup includes shared Kanban board data. Verify archives contain at least:
